race.comment: CAFE AU LAIT (4) resumes with strong claims. She's a promising filly who went to the paddock as a maiden winner at Seymour, backed into $1.80 there having tested a talented one prior. Expect she measures up to this. SUGAR SCHNAPPS (1) comes over to Australia now with the Hayes yard having won her maiden at Arawa Park in New Zealand last time out. She draws well and gets D Lane aboard, have to respect. BODY OF VENUS (3) resumes, now with the Andrew Noblet yard. She's trialled well and has the ability to be figuring here from an ideal draw. REGAL SECRET (6) is going okay. The run two back at Pakenham has her in the mix.
